pr_title: Add challenge phase detail edit feature for more fields
pr_body:
Add challenge phase detail edit feature for following fields:

- [x] allowed submission file types
- [x] maximum concurrent submissions
- [x] phase visibility
- [x] submission visibility
- [x] <s> default meta attributes </s>

pr_title: Lazy load tabs on challenge-list page
pr_body:
Till now, we were eagerly loading the tabs on `challenge-list` pages . But now the content in a tab are lazy-loaded i.e. they are only loaded when the user visits a particular tab. This will lower the time for a particular page/tab.

@Ram81 @Kajol-Kumari

pr_title: Fix leaderboard polling logic
pr_body:
There were two problems in the polling of the leaderboard.

1. There are multiple simultaneous requests while polling the leaderboard
2. When a user leaves the challenge component and visits it again the poller is started automatically (without going to leaderboard tab)

### Fixes

1. The cause of the issue was `selectPhaseSplit` was getting called twice, [1](https://github.com/Cloud-CV/EvalAI/blob/master/frontend_v2/src/app/components/challenge/challengeleaderboard/challengeleaderboard.component.ts#L307) and [2](https://github.com/Cloud-CV/EvalAI/blob/master/frontend_v2/src/app/components/utility/selectphase/selectphase.component.html#L76). 
Fixed it by making routing changes for the child component and using `selectPhaseSplit` in the parent component.

2. Added a condition for the poller to start only if the user is at specific phase split's leaderboard.

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/24366008/118995980-31223580-b9a5-11eb-97fb-b43f91a93da7.mp4



@Ram81 @Kajol-Kumari

pr_title: Fix team filter on All submissions page
pr_body:
**Problem**: When we filter the team name on all submission page, the data is different than expected. It is because whichever api call is taking the most time that is being displayed on the page.

**Fix**:

1. Fixed it by checking if the api call for data displayed is same as entered.
2. The pagination of filter submissions is also fixed. Since the pagination number is taken from the URL and when we filter the team name, the URL changes as well.


https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/24366008/119237574-2b6e5080-bb5b-11eb-8bbb-5d5a674dc281.mp4

pr_title: Fix worker-logs error notification
pr_body:
***Error:*** 
```
GET http://localhost:8000/api/challenges/undefined/get_worker_logs/

HttpErrorResponse {headers: HttpHeaders, status: 404, statusText: "Not Found", url: "http://localhost:8000/api/challenges/undefined/get_worker_logs/", ok: false, …}
```

***Fix:***

`fetchWorkerLogs()` was called before we get the `challenge.id`, therefore the error was being seen.

@Ram81 @Kajol-Kumari
